    VALIDATION GATE:
        ✅ all_10_PHASE_validation_gates passed (including Phase 0: DSL + Capabilities)
        ✅ workspace_configuration discovered FROM ai-workscape.prompt.cfg
        ✅ agent_sequence_definition supports dynamic agent_count
        ✅ execution_mode classified FOR all agents
        ✅ context configured (fork OR normal) FOR all agents
        ✅ all_agents documented WITH methodologies
        ✅ handoff_protocol established WITH dynamic_paths AND execution_mode
        ✅ workflow_coordination_sequence built WITH hybrid_execution
        ✅ parallel_execution_rule enforced
        ✅ sequential_execution_rule enforced
        ✅ context_forking_rule enforced
        ✅ checklist_integration configured WITH semantic_extensions
        ✅ phase_documentation_templates created WITH execution_mode
        ✅ skill_integration_protocol established
        ✅ workflow_principles articulated INCLUDING hybrid_execution
        ✅ template assembled successfully
        ✅ customization_guide included
        ✅ no_hardcoded_paths remaining
        ✅ dynamic_agent_scaling supported
        ✅ CFG_DSL_compliant throughout
        ✅ all_filenames UPPERCASE.md enforced
        ✅ all_content agent_oriented PAG_DSL enforced
        ✅ handoff_context_structure defined WITH execution_mode
        ✅ user_rules_integration supported
        ✅ error_recovery_protocol defined
        ✅ output_location standardized TO .agent-workspace/.agent-workflow/
        ✅ forking_spec integrated
        ✅ abilities_spec integrated

# PHASE 11: Always Rules

ALWAYS read DSL specification files FIRST (Phase 0)
ALWAYS read forking specification (.claude/_AGENT-FORKING.md)
ALWAYS read abilities specification (.claude/_CLAUDE-ABILITIES.md)
ALWAYS discover workspace_config FROM ai-workscape.prompt.cfg
ALWAYS use workspace_zones FOR artifact_paths
ALWAYS create filenames AS UPPERCASE.md
ALWAYS write content AS agent_oriented PAG_DSL
ALWAYS classify agents AS parallel OR sequential
ALWAYS set context: fork FOR discovery/investigation agents
ALWAYS set context: normal FOR action agents
ALWAYS use Task tool WITH subagent_type parameter
ALWAYS execute parallel agents IN single message WITH multiple Task calls
ALWAYS execute sequential agents ONE at a time
ALWAYS include execution_mode IN handoff signals
ALWAYS include context_used IN handoff signals
ALWAYS support Skill tool invocation
ALWAYS document skill usage patterns
NEVER create human_documentation IN workflow files
NEVER use taxonomy_based_extensions (use .md only)
NEVER hardcode file_paths OR workspace_locations
ALWAYS define agent_sequence WITH dynamic_count
NEVER skip handoff_protocol documentation
ALWAYS include artifact_structure WITH config_based_paths
NEVER omit orchestration_rules
ALWAYS specify checklist_integration
NEVER forget validation_gates
ALWAYS document workflow_principles INCLUDING hybrid_execution
NEVER assume manual_agent_coordination
ALWAYS include customization_instructions
NEVER use ambiguous agent_responsibilities
ALWAYS support arbitrary agent_count FROM 1 TO N
ALWAYS use Task tool FOR agent execution (NEVER simulate)
ALWAYS define handoff_context WITH PAG_DSL structure
ALWAYS include user_rules IN handoff IF PROVIDED
ALWAYS implement error_recovery WITH WEBSEARCH + retry
ALWAYS apply delete_and_rewrite FOR file_modification_errors
ALWAYS execute recovery_automatically WITHOUT user_intervention
NEVER re_read_file AFTER modification_error WITHOUT delete_first
NEVER ask_permission FOR tool_error_recovery
ALWAYS write output TO .agent-workspace/.agent-workflow/
ALWAYS prompt user FOR first_time_initiation approval
NEVER reference outdated_workspace_structures
ALWAYS generate CFG_DSL_compliant output
NEVER mix narrative_documentation WITH DSL_directives
NEVER use abstract_verbs WITHOUT tool_mapping
ALWAYS batch parallel agents IN single message
NEVER simulate agent execution IN orchestrator
ALWAYS use context: fork FOR research/discovery/investigation
ALWAYS preserve all v1 functionality WHILE adding v2 capabilities
